DENGUE/DHF UPDATE 2004 (18)
***************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
[This is by no means a comprehensive collection of all reports of
dengue in the world since the last update. In order to make it more
inclusive, ProMED-mail asks readers to send reports of dengue
outbreaks that they find to <promed@promedmail.org>]
In this update:
[1] Venezuela
[2] Sri Lanka
[3] Viet Nam
*****
[1] Venezuela
Date: Sat, 19 Jun 2004 18:55:41 -0400
From: Alfonso Rodriguez <arodriguezm@SaludFMV.org>
Source: Ministry of Health of Venezuela, Epidemiological Bulletin, 19
Jun 2004 Epidemiological Week No.21, 2004 (May 23-29, 2004) [in
Spanish, summarized by AR; edited]
<http://www.msds.gov.ve/msdsnew/logros/Alerta/Alertas2004/Alerta21.zip>

For the week ending 29 May 2004, the Venezuelan Ministry of Health
reported 512 cases of dengue, for a year-to-date total of 15 559
cases, triple the number for the same period of 2003 (5734).
In the same week there were 27 cases of DHF (5.3 percent) with no
deaths, for a cumulative total of 955 cases of DHF with 3 deaths.
The dengue case trend has been increasing over the last 6 weeks. All
4 types of dengue are co-circulating.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
******
[2] Sri Lanka
Date: Sun, 20 Jun 2004 00:11:20 +0900 (JST)
From: ProMED <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: ColomboPage News Desk, Sri Lanka Sat 19 Jun 2004 [edited]
<http://www.colombopage.com/archive/June19122422UN.html>

Dengue takes 33 lives and affects over 5000 more
------------------------------------------------
The Department of Epidemic Diseases at the Health Ministry reports
that dengue fever has spread seriously in the country. Already 33
deaths have been reported [in 2004].
A spokesperson said the reported number of dengue patients is 5434 so
far, and the disease is seriously spreading in the Anuradhapura,
Matale, Galle, Matara, and Puttlam Districts. The largest number of
deaths, 10 persons, was reported from the Colombo District.
The spokesperson also said that though actions have been taken to
slow the spread of the disease, public support has not been given as
expected. Circulars have been issued with instructions to health
authorities, local authorities and regional authorities to implement
preventive care programmes in affected districts.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
******
[3] Viet Nam
Date: Mon, 14 Jun 2004 10:31:25 -0400
From: ProMED <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Reuters, Jakarta Post 14 Jun 2004 [edited]
<http://www.thejakartapost.com/detaillatestnews.asp?
fileid=20040614190852&irec=4>

Dengue infections triple in Viet Nam
---------------------
Dengue fever infections in Viet Nam have tripled to 15 923 cases
during the 2nd quarter of the calendar year, taking deaths from the
disease this year [2004] to 29, state media reported on Monday.
Around 10 people died from the mosquito-borne disease and 5350 more
were infected during the period from January to March. Officials of
the health ministry said most of the infections were concentrated in
southern Viet Nam, the Lao Dong (Labor) daily said.
The health ministry is holding an emergency meeting in southern Viet
Nam this week to find ways to fight the deadly disease, the report
said.
Dengue fever, which is carried by the _Aedes aegypti_ mosquito and
normally hits tropical Viet Nam each year from the start of the rainy
season in April.
